jane mendillo born jane l mendillo new britain connecticut us residence concord massachusetts us alma mater yale university occupation investor endowment manager and philanthropist years active   present known for managing the endowments of wellesley college and harvard university salary us million  jane l mendillo is an american investor endowment fund manager and philanthropist she was the president and chief executive officer of the harvard management company charged with managing harvard universitys endowment she led the investment team from  to  leaving the endowment at us billion previous to her leading the company she was in charge of managing the endowments domestic equities venture capital charitable trusts and gifts during her first couple of years at harvard she gained the attention of the investment team at wellesley college and was tapped to be the colleges chief investment officera position she filled from  to  leaving the endowment at  billion up from its  market value of  billion in the summer of  she returned to harvard to lead its investment committee her time at harvard was marked by the financial crisis of  as well as under performing positions in private equity in  forbes magazines  most powerful women list placed mendillo as number  before margaret chan and after hillary clinton early life and educationedit jane mendillo was born in new britain connecticut she has a ba from yale college in  with a degree in english and an mba from the yale school of management in  investment careeredit previous to her graduating with a mba she worked in the office of investments at yale university from  to  under david f swensen she is a cfa charterholder during  she worked with lord abbett in new york as an equities analyst jane mendollo was a management consultant with bain  company in boston from  to  harvard beginningsedit jane was employed by the harvard management company from  she occupied various roles such as vice president of external management in which she had investment responsibility for  billion in harvard assets including  billion in externally managed investments for the harvard endowment and  billion in harvard pension and related accounts jane’s other positions at harvard management included domestic equities investment venture capital investment and the management and investment of charitable trusts and gifts wellesleys endowmentedit after her time at harvard she was tapped by wellesley college to join their investment team she was the chief investment officer at wellesley college from  to  and was responsible for the investment policy and management of the college’s  billion endowment and its related assets she increased the colleges endowment from  billion to  billion usd return to harvards endowmentedit mendillo spent  years at the harvard management company leaving in  as its chief executive officer she returned to harvard as its president and chief executive officer on july   and was responsible for directing its  billion endowment she assumed the endowment before the  financial crisis and kept the universitys liquidity above standards but conceded a sharp  decrease in market value plunging the endowment by  billion  billion to  billion during the late  crisis the college had to borrow  billion to cover costs so as to not redeploy or close postions early as markets recovered in  and  the endowment posted positive returns  and  respectively her capital gains in fiscal year  was profiled by the colleges magazine as a net gain of  billion for the endowment raising it from  billion to  billion leaving only  billion in total losses since her assumption of the endowment her investment strategies in  yielded a  return leaving it valued at  billion she characterized the year as a period of choppy and highly sensitive markets despite the dip in market value the endowment marked its third year of surpassing the colleges policy portfolio benchmark in  the endowment was up  to  billion and exceeded portfollio bench marks by nearly  at the conclusion of the  fiscal year it was accouned that the endowmented posted a gain of  rasing the value to  billion the largest in the ivy league the endowment over her tenure suffered substantial losses in private equity investments but exceeded target returns on real assets and commodities overall the harvard endowment fell below that of its peers in terms of capital gains harvard magazine reported in  that mendillo was compensated  million in the  fiscal year according to a  article by bloomberg markets her compensation from  to  rose significantly starting at approximately  million eventually leading to a compensation package of  million in  she stepped down from managing harvards endowment in  stating i feel like i’ve accomplished a lot of what i set out to accomplish later commenting that the organization and portfolio are doing well the trajectory is positive mendillo led the endowment through the  financial crisis and  choppy aftermath mitigating total losses to a net value of  million personal lifeedit jane lives in concord massachusetts with her husband ralph earle iii and their two children elizabeth and thomas mendillo is a member of the boston security analysts society she is a member of the yale university investment committee a member of the board of the investment fund for foundations and a corporator of emerson hospital forbes magazine included mendillo in the  most powerful women list of  referencesedit  a b wellesly annual report pdf   a b the  most powerful women forbescom   harvard management company announces fiscal  results harvard gazette retrieved    harvard borrows  billion the costs and rationale harvard magazine  retrieved    harvard endowment rises  billion to  billion harvard magazine  retrieved    harvard university endowment yields flat return for fiscal  harvard gazette retrieved    harvard university endowment earns  return for fiscal year harvard gazette retrieved    harvard university endowment delive